            "lemma": "\u03c8\u03c5\u03c7\u1f75",
            "xlit": "psych\u1e17",
            "pronunciation": "psoo-khay'",
            "kjv_def": "heart (+ -ily), life, mind, soul, + us, + you.",
            "pspeech": "N-AFS",
            "description": " breath, i.e. (by implication) spirit, abstractly or concretely (the animal sentient principle only; thus distinguished on the one hand from \u03c0\u03bd\u03b5\u1fe6\u03bc\u03b1(pne\u00fbma), which is the rational and immortal soul; and on the other from \u03b6\u03c9\u1f75(z\u014d\u1e17), which is mere vitality, even of plants: these terms thus exactly correspond respectively to the Hebrew \u05e0\u05b6\u05e4\u05b6\u05e9\u05c1(nephesh), \u05e8\u05d5\u05bc\u05d7\u05b7(r\u00fbwach) and \u05d7\u05b7\u05d9(chay))"
